name: Bendungan Palasari
address: Taman Wana Street, Ekasari, Kec. Melaya, Kabupaten Jembrana, Bali 82252, Indonesia
review 1: Doesn't appear to have anything to mitigate the effects in the local fish, as they try ti jump up the dam unsuccessfully. Usually dams will have a fish ladder installed or pumps to allow the fish to continue to migrate
review 2: Fascinating view up there, to see this dam even though the water volume seems the lowest debit at this time. Not many activities besides the locals try some luck for fishing and some people spending time there like me.
review 3: Hidden gem in the west of Bali! Possibility to go on a private boat tour around the lake for only 100k (ask for Koman) during which we saw many different birds and monitor lizards. A must see!
review 4: It's a nice place to visit with calming view of rainforest and hills
review 5: Calm and beautiful place. A perfect place for locals to hangout in the afternoon
